<br>
-You can never mend and kill yourself.  If you have 3 hp and you fail a mend and it hurts you instead of heals then it will take you down to 1 hp.  This isn't the worst thing on earth but it sucks when some random mob comes up and hits you once and you die.  <br>
<br>
-In my experience your AC/hp/agi are the most important stats for a monk.  The higher the AC you have the less damage you take when you get hit.  The higher the sta and the better the hp gear the longer you will live.  (high lvl monks have much much less hp than warriors or other tank classes.  I have 1627 hp at lvl 52 with ok gear.)  A high agility effects how often you are hit and also how ofter your abilities like dodge and block work.  Keeping your agi well above 100 is a very good idea.  This leaves str that I haven't commented on.  In my opinion it is the least important stat for a monk compared to the rest.  The difference between having 110 str and 130 str really isn't very noticable.  In groups you will have a str buff most of the time anyways so it isn't a stat I worry about too much.  I believe my stats are currently:<br>
128 str<br>
104 sta<br>
124 agi<br>
115 dex<br>
<br>
Dex effects how fast you gain weapon skills like 1hb, h2h, 2hb and also determines how often a weapon will proc a special ability.  <br>
<br>
-As some of the others have said keeping all your weapon skills maxed is very important.  Even though 1hb is the best you can find at lower to mid levels once you get your epic your fists will become 9/16 and you will own stuff.  2hb lets you deal out massive amounts of damage but also gets you massive amounts of agro so be careful when using it in a group.  <br>
<br>
-You also want to practice mend and fiegn death as much as you can until they are maxed.  If you aren't pulling then just fiegn death over and over till it is maxed for your lvl.  If you are selling something in EC or riding a boat or whatever you should always keep those two skills maxed to the best of your ability.  Just to let you know.  You can gain skill in mend even if you already have full hp.  So, feel free to click it any time it pops unless you have it above 100 skill and are using it soloing.  A very important fact about fiegn death is that it will fail automatically if autoattack is on when you fiegn.  ALWAYS turn autoattack off before you fiegn death or the mob will continue beating on you till FD pops again.  Also if a mob is casting a spell on you and you fiegn death the spell will still be casted on you.  This will always break your fiegn and the mob will agro on you again.  I know it is painful sometimes but you have to let the spell hit you before you fiegn and before the mob starts casting another spell on you.<br>
<br>
-Once i got instill doubt up to 200 skill i started using it to fear kite mobs in DL.  You need j-boots or some other run speed increase spell to do it though.  I could easily fear kite and kill SG's at lvl 40.  This is something that takes a lot of practice.  This is also VERY important.  If you want to instill doubt something you must not click any other ability (flying kick etc...) while the instill doubt is working.  If your other ability attack button is down when you would normally do your instill doubt kick then it will fail automatically.<br>
<br>
-I'm not sure what your playing style is like but some monks stay in groups non-stop and always hide behind a tank.  This is the wrong way to level if you want to be effective at all at higher lvls.  You really need to get the agro a lot to build up your defense, dodge, block, riposte...If you solo or tank often than you should have no problem keeping these maxed.  I have around 962 ac unbuffed at lvl 52 with decent gear.  With very uber gear and having your defense maxed out a monk can tank very well.  They just can't taunt =p  <br>
<br>
-In my opinion Wu's fighting armor is about 3 times better than cresant armor.  cresant armor is very low AC.  I believe it is as low if not lower than cured silk armor.  <br>
<br>
-aside from CC you can also hunt in runnyeye at a lower level since it has a bank and vendors you can sell to using sneak.<br>
<br>
